  <!-- ── Troubleshooting ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">If something isn't working</h2>
    <ul class="gs-tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Claude says it can't find the project folder.</strong>
        Make sure you selected the <strong>ux-prototyping</strong> folder itself — not a folder
        inside it. If you're not sure which one to pick, open GitHub Desktop, go to
        <strong>Repository → Show in Finder</strong> (Mac) or <strong>Show in Explorer</strong>
        (Windows), and that will open exactly the right folder. Then go back to Claude Code and
        select that same folder.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Claude starts a review but immediately hits an error.</strong>
        The most likely cause is Chrome not being connected. Open Chrome, click the Claude icon
        in the top-right of the browser, and check that it says <em>Connected</em> — not
        <em>Sign in</em> or <em>Disconnected</em>. If it's not connected, sign in with your
        Claude account. Chrome must be open and connected for page reviews to work.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The report saved but isn't appearing on the site.</strong>
        Reports need to be published manually after saving. Log into Altitude and trigger a
        deploy, or ask Richard Gill to do it. Claude saves the report automatically — the
        publishing step is separate and always manual.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A tool isn't appearing in the / command list.</strong>
        Type <strong>/skill-creator</strong> in Claude Code and repeat the install step for
        that tool only (the prompts are in step 8 above). Make sure the ux-prototyping folder
        is open as your project when you do.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Can I just use Claude in my browser instead of the desktop app?</strong>
        For general questions, yes. But the browser version of Claude can't save files or
        publish anything to the site. For anything that produces a saved report, you need the
        desktop app with the project folder open.
      </li>
    </ul>
